—ЩNarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/decode.mdЩ@c10709ffb8db1b43632e1d0473b251654d8cad2814a1d45f7d15715cb4478242­title: decode‘ЁExamplesЪDecode the output of an external command
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> ^cat myfile.q | decode utf-8


```
Decode an UTF-16 string into nushell UTF-8 string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[00 53 00 6F 00 6D 00 65 00 20 00 44 00 61 00 74 00 61] | decode utf-16be
Some Data

```
’ђђЪ>Title: title: decode
Path: Examples
Content:
Decode the output of an external command
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> ^cat myfile.q | decode utf-8


```
Decode an UTF-16 string into nushell UTF-8 string
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[00 53 00 6F 00 6D 00 65 00 20 00 44 00 61 00 74 00 61] | decode utf-16be
Some Data

```
—ЩNarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/decode.mdЩ@027e5450f6741c39e6b744d077be49e4d29ebcb417d095d98702cffcc0c25130­title: decode‘ҐNotesЪMultiple encodings are supported; here are a few:

big5, euc-jp, euc-kr, gbk, iso-8859-1, utf-16, cp1252, latin5
For a more complete list of encodings please refer to the encoding_rs

documentation link at https://docs.rs/encoding_rs/latest/encoding_rs/#statics
